resources.description: Gas DAO is a polling platform that conducts Web3 market surveys based on scientific methods, among a dynamic group of on-chain identified, incentivized active Ethereum users, that currently counts ~45K different addresses.Launched on December 29th, 2021, the DAO targets mainly Web3 protocols, offering them cleaned survey data files, automated and human analysis into identified survey trends and sub-groups.The identity of survey respondents is set by their mandatory sign-in with their Ethereum wallet, and enriched as they supply demographic information, that is used to enhance survey validity and insights.The DAO's surveys' data is stored "... in a centralized database owned by the Gas DAO Insights team and shared with partners. Centralized storage is deemed essential, as it is to allow the generation of cryptographically verifiable demographic data at scale". One of the DAO's most important assets is therefore its aggregated list of curated Ethereum identities.The GAS token serves both survey activities and governance, and ecosystem participants are typically also DAO shareholders. The Gas DAO community votes via off-chain Snapshot, and governs on-chain mainly through voting delegation.

resources.name: Instadapp
resources.description: Instadapp is a cross-DeFi asset and investments manager. It aims to supply individual and group traders with a simple UI for complex DeFi trades, including an inbuilt Flash Loans aggregator. To developers, it offers a modular environment for extensions and integrations.At the heart of the protocol stands the "DeFi Smart Layer" (DSL) - a middleware between DeFi traders, developers and protocols, which has been evolving since Instadapp's 2019 establishment. The DSL onboards users via Web3 applications (wallet or other), by user-set permissions, to their Instadapp Smart Account whereby they can compare and buy on various DeFi lego combinations.Trading platforms integrations are served via DSL's core Connectors, which, combined with basic inbuilt functions, make extensions a matter of Web2 programming rather than Smart contracts coding.Instadapp's governance token was publicly  launched in June 2021, to control DSL and other protocol decisions by community off-chain signaling and binding on-chain decision-making.

Enzyme Finance is a protocol for DeFi asset management and investments. Its non-custodial, forkable "Funds" offer permissionless participation in tracked, transparent strategies of investment combinations.
      Enzyme is among DeFi pioneers. It was founded in July 2016 as a Swiss company called Melonport AG, successfully ICO'd its MLN trading token in March 2017, and has since integrated multiple tokens and tooling. In early 2019, Melonport self-dissolved and handed authority of the protocol over to the Melon Council. The project rebranded to Enzyme in Dec. 2020, while sticking with $MLN. 
      Enzyme's two Council DAOs, "Melon Council" and "Enzyme Council", are actually one and the same institution evolved over time, and the governor of the Enzyme project on Web3. It is mandated to nurture and guard the protocol, its products and ecosystem.
      Thus, the (Aragon-based) Melon Council DAO, of founders and early business partners, had served as Melon's governor up until rebranding. It was smoothly inherited by the (currently Snapshot) Enzyme Council DAO, with 6 of the 9 original member addresses still serving, as does MGM - one of the Council's 2 original governance tokens.
      The Council is "bound by fiduciary duties, guiding principles and Enzyme Council Statutes" (from documentation). It currently operates through a number of specialized teams who come under either the Enzyme Technical Council or the Enzyme User Representatives group.

resources.name: Decentraland
resources.description: Decentraland and the DAODecentraland DAO, powered by Ethereum and Aragon, is the main governor of Decentraland ‚Äì a platform of a shared virtual world ("metaverse"). It was introduced in 2015 as "‚Ä¶ a proof of concept for allocating ownership of digital real estates on a blockchain."During August to December 2017 It held a first sale of its MANA token and an auction of LAND parcels, the platform's virtual plots over which users create, exhibit and consume various VR elements.Decentraland went fully public in Feb. 2020, along with the DAO. It is a unique example of a DAO running a non-financial online project, deciding various critical aspects of the game, including ground rules, by its users. Some key community governance functionskey community governance functions are also available for the voters and voting power is gained by an elaborate mechanism combining MANA wrapping and ownership of game objects.Numeric IndicatorsSize: In April 2021, Decentraland reportedly hosted some 10,000 daily active users. With weekly sales between 280K-3M $US. It now ranks as the 12th largest NFT collection on DappRadar and the largest metaverse by a margin.The price of 1 parcel of virtual land opened at 1,000 MANA (~106 USD) at Decentraland‚Äôs first (2017) LAND auction. Currently, parcels of LAND may be bought for anywhere between 4,000 and 30,000 MANA (at 1 MANA around 1.2 USD). The most expensive plot yet sold in March 2018 for 2,000,000 MANA.Voting: The DAO registers 109 voting proposals since its Jan. 2020 inception.How Do I join Decentraland?To just wander around Decentraland, one may enter as a guest, pick a graphic avatar and some basic features, connect a validatable email to it, and set off to explore. To use most of Decentraland‚Äôs features, though, one must connect a (preferably browser-based) crypto wallet to the avatar, with at least 100 MANA and some Ether for transfer fees. Upon sending the MANA, one is allowed to set the avatar‚Äôs name, and jump in.TokensMANA is Decentraland‚Äôs (ERC-20 standard) fungible, fully tradable token. Owning 100 MANA is minimum to register as a user. Paying (~4000+) MANA is the only way to acquire a Decentrland plot of land. MANA is earned, spent, and traded for platform collectibles and services.LAND (ERC-721 is Decentraland‚Äôs NFT, transferable for MANA on the platform. 1 LAND represents 1 individual Decentraland parcel - a specific plot of 16*16 virtual meters in the metaverse where users may build and exhibit their content. The platform‚Äôs (currently only) city of Genesis consists of 90,601 parcels, all tradable save for Plazas and Roads.MANA and LAND represent still more than their trade values: they also set DAO governance - the decision-making power of participants in the DAO community.GovernanceDecentraland Governance gives voters control over policy agenda and decision-making, the rules that instruct them and the institutions authorized to enact those rules.The Decentraland platform hosts numerous autonomous users and varied, content-reach sub-projects - members‚Äô VR partnerships and creations, as well as a teeming marketplace and quite a few trademarks.The DAO runs two main governance mechanisms:Community governanceThe DAO‚Äôs community proposal-making and voting interface is powered by Aragon‚Äôs Govern. A community decision accepted in March 2021 instructs that the DAO implement and oversee a Snapshot space for binding off-chain governance, to tackle rising gas fees.Minimum threshold to proceed to community voting: 1% support and 25% approval among threshold voters; Minimum to pass: 20% support and 66% of all casted votes.The Security Advisory BoardThe board was initially appointed by the Decentraland team. It is mandated to safeguard the DAO‚Äôs citircal governance functions, block harmful updates, and address emergencies.The Board examines every community proposal once it has passed the voting threshold, and may delay or reject it: Each of the five members of the Boardholds individual veto power in every decision, as a multiple backup emergency break. The Board also operates community voting, finance and some other functions until they are properly secured.Minimum Board support to approve a proposal: 60% and zero dissent. Some types of proposals approved by the Security Board must be forwarded to- and enacted by governance body #3, namely: the Decentraland Foundation.The Decentraland FoundationThe Foundation, aka Decentraland Company, is an independent non-profit established next to the DAO to foster Decentraland‚Äôs network's "decentralization" and "neutrality". It was allocated 222M MANA. It also owns the property rights of Decentraland‚Äôs unique assets.Being the platform's legally accountable arm, it represents a set of off-chain governance demands which bind the entire Decentraland framework. Other governance elements include an elaborated code of ethics, a significant content policy, and a blunt privacy policy- legally and on-chain binding norms of the Decentraland culture.

    The Synthetix organization works through five designated DAOs (See in project documentation):
    - Synthetix Treasury DAO is set to ensure that all Synthetix governing bodies remain incentivised to support its ecosystem development.
    - Synthetix Spartan DAO: Community-elected, set to manage the Synthetix multi-DAO space. Among other tasks, it is responsible for proposal deliberation, protocol change coordination, and hosting community governance meetings.
    - Synthetix Protocol DAO: Owner of the Synthetix Protocol core contracts. Responsible for upgrading and releasing new contracts on behalf of the Spartan Council. Its membership is Council-permissioned by defined criteria.
    - Synthetix Ambassador DAO: Members here are Synthetix delegates, who get staked-empowered by the community through this DAO so as to meta-govern Synthetix-owned DeFi assets in their native governance DAOs.

It generates user-specified "Gardens" - tokenized liquidity pools of investor groups that propose, vote and manage specific yield & risk strategies, built over a scope of tools and integrations.Currently on Beta phase and approaching public launch, authority of Babylon lays mainly in the hands of the team & consultant multisig. $BABL holders' authority over the project is announced to assume multisig's responsibilities as the protocol gets battle-tested and stabilized.By generating Gardens, Babylon effectively functions as a launcher of investment DAOs, with a centralized aspect to those as Garden Creators hold the authority to set their Garden members' permissions. While Garden parameters allow to prevent the execution of flash-loans, no documented mention was found of binding restrictions or a vetting process for Gardens' strategies. Such and other risks are explicitly delegated to protocol users, specifically liquidity providers.

resources.name: Spice DAO
resources.description: The Spice DAO (aka "Dune DAO") is a Web3 production studio publishing sci-fi animation and NFTs from established writers and artists. It was established to create an NFT-limited animation series inspired by an extended manuscript for the 1955 novel Dune, by Frank Herbert.The extended manuscript, referred to as the "Dune Bible", was created by Alejandro Jodorowsky. The DAO has bootstrapped its activity via a crowdfunding campaign to bid on a rare original copy of that Bible. It has won the 22 Nov., 2021  auction totaling 2,608 ETH in donations, of which 784 remained after the purchase commitment and main expanses. Auction donations were monetized based on their shares in the form of $SPICE, the DAO's erc-20 token, that also serves its Snapshot governance. On-chain transactions are signed by the DAO's multisig.Jodorowsky's 1975 printed Bible, including hundreds of images and storyboards, would have made a 14-hour film. It was already cast with Orson Welles, Salvador Dali and others, and partially fundraised for by Jodorowsky himself. Production efforts eventually failed because no studio would carry the financial burden involved. The Bible nevertheless came to acquire a significant influence on science fiction films and subculture.Ownership of the Bible copy does not grant copyrights, and carries different questions of legal stewardship that are being addressed by the DAO. Regardless, the Bible serves Spice DAO as a symbolic asset and a source of inspiration.

resources.name: KeeperDAO
resources.description: KeeperDAO's protocol is built to outperform DeFi bots who compete for crypto trading opportunities in pending blockchain transactions. Such competition typically also elevates network gas prices. Opportunity and higher-than-standard gas profits mostly go to network miners, hence aka Miner Extractable Value (MEV).The DAO introduces a pooled decentralized network of traders and liquidity that operates its own opportunity-seeking bots - "Keepers".The network replaces the above-described bot competition with a model of secret, wrapped coordination to keep members' operations under Ethereum bot radars. Network Cooperation is further incentivized by pooled opportunity-seeking resources, profit sharing on consensus-algorithm best bids, and network (token) governance over the protocol.

resources.name: Constitution
resources.description:

It raised over $40M but not enough to win, upon which the DAO multisig suggested full reimbursement (-gas fees) to tokenholders, and emptied its treasury. Follow-up governance memes and projects currently keep the idea & token alive. 
    - a trust experiment: high donations suggest that the open identification of acknowledged crypto figures with the project overcame the vague nature of its multisig commitments. 
    - a meme campaign: while not winning the auction, the carefully selected performance generated high traction to the idea of people sovereignty.
    - See the fundraising campaign, auction.

resources.name: FreeRossDAO
resources.description: FreeRossDAO is dedicated to the release of Mr. Ross Ulbricht from his life imprisonment in the U.S., served for establishing and running the anonymous, online, crypto-based Silk Road drug market. The DAO was bootstrapped through a December 2021 bid on an NFT-minted collection of Ulbricht's artworks. If Ulbricht is released, The DAO intends to "... use leftover funds raised to free Ross and advance prison reform."DAO decision-making begins with discussions and voted proposals on Discord, to be formulated and reviewed by an Advisory Council, and if ratified there, moved to community Snapshot voting and DAO multisig / Operations execution.The DAO's ongoing campaign is much into real-life activities such as media productions and mass letter-writing, a well-known human rights practice traditionally associated with political prisoners and with the establishment of Amnesty International. Mr. Ulbricht's personal circle is related to the on-chain efforts as well. Such hybrid, Web3-Web2-real-life formats of political organizing seem to be a growing trend, facilitated by advancements in DAO, NFT, DeFi and community tooling.Mr. Ulbricht was imprisoned for his role as creator, owner and operator of the Silk Road online market, that utilized Tor and $BTC to facilitate illegal sales of narcotics and more. He was charged and convicted of Narcotic Trafficing Conspiracy, Continuing Criminal Enterprise, Computer Hacking Conspiracy, and Money Laundering Conspiracy.The records of Ulbricht's liberatarian ideology support his version according to which Silk Road was motivated by a wish to allow drug purchasing as a matter of personal choice, as "... people should have the right to buy and sell whatever they wanted so long as they weren't hurting anyone else." (see Ulbricht's 2015 letter to Judge Forrest upon his sentencing)The FreeRossDAO and other supporters quote this ideology at the basis for their campaign, alongside the significant role of Silk Road in the rise of Bitcoin.In his letter to the Judge, Mr. Ulbricht repented his short-sightedness and irresponsible methods, and the consequential harms brought upon drug addicts and his close circles. However, his plea to be released at some point in life was denied. His case lost before a Second Circle court of appeals in May 2017, and was denied a request for review by the U.S. Supreme Court on 28 June 2018.

resources.name: AssangeDAO
resources.description: AssangeDAO is set to "inspire a powerful solidarity network and fight for the freedom of Julian Assange", by raising funds to help with his legal fees and campaigns, and to increase public awareness "on the systemic failure of our justice systems." (quotes: project website)The DAO was bootstrapped via a public auction of the Censored dynamic NFT created by Pak. Censored continuously counts the days Mr. Assange has spent behind bars. Its 1/1 unique edition was auctioned on Feb. 8th-9th of 2022, alongside an openly mintable one. The winning bid for the 1/1 Censored, made by AssangeDAO, was 16,593.05878 ETH - all raised during the DAO's 5-days, designated crowdfunding campaign.A total of 29K+ funders thereby received the DAO's native $JUSTICE token, proportionally to their bid contributions.Censored sale funds were then donated back by Pak "... in their entirety to Assange's legal defense fund and Free Assange campaign efforts." (DAO homepage) This donation was transacted via the Wau Holland Foundation, that still holds most of the funds pending strategic and operative decisions. The foundation is described by AssangeDAO as a close partner in its mission.AssangeDAO is currently governed by $JUSTICE holders on Snapshot, and by an operative multisig that includes identified DAOists. Openly inspired by the ConstitutionDAO and FreeRossDAO operations, it leverages ecosystem trust in identified leaders to gather a supportive community behind a Greater-Good purpose (one that extends beyond community's self-interests).Another notable organ in this ecosystem is the DAO's Consensus Unit (aka Advisory Council / Assange Family), consisting of Mr. Assange's lawyer and family, and some DAO members. The Unit is mandated to screen all Snapshot proposals "... for any potential harm to Assange or his legal case", and veto where such is found (project homepage).As part of its governance-building process, the DAO's 3rd decision from early March 2022 debated whether to "confirm or revoke" that authority of the Consensus Unit. The support of a great majority of Members for keeping the Unit's power in place highlights the human aspect of DAOs.AssangeDAO thus also demonstrates the flexibility achieved by the DAO format so as to advanced hybrids as such, that is a (a) formal blockchain organization, that's (b) governed by its token-holders, still (c) voluntarily fully surrenders to the decisions of a 100% off-chain group, while (4) storing its funds with yet another, private legal entity. Notably, this organizational sophistication paves the ground for an interplay of legitimacy sources, namely: community, token-share, personal and organizational reputation, kinship, and the trust-less-trust of blockchains.While the effective management of such potentials will always be an ongoing task for any social movement, still their availability through Web3 tools is probably worth the attention of political activists everywhere.

resources.name: elimu.ai
resources.description: elimu.ai is building and distributing FOSS educational apps/games to teach basic literacy and arithmetic to disadvantaged children around the world.It uses AI to adjust content & progress to individual learners, and the $ELIMU token to align donators, investors and developers around mission and decision-making. "Elimu" is the Swahili word for "education".elimu.ai first established its Github project as early as 2015, and has diversified in a few waves of development since, with tens of thousands of R & D hours put-in by over 50 contributors, as testified a project leader in a conversation with DD.During its early phases, the project served personalized learning through face recognition verification. This has since changed to a strategy of device distribution - a platform-loaded tablet or smartphone for every learner.On 2018, elimu.ai was selected among the 11 semifinalist teams in the XPRIZE global learning competition. In June 2020 it has DAOed and tokenized its operation through Aragon, and about a year later upgraded to its current Aragon Govern and Aragon Voice systems. Since DeepDAO still does not serve governance data for the latter, it is currently presented only for the organization's older Aragon account.The project currently reports to have distributed its applications for small-group testing in Tanzania and Kenya (Swahili language), with children in India (in Hindi) and the Philippines (Filipino) being next on its roadmap.

resources.name: Jenny Metaverse DAO
resources.description:
The Jenny (also: Jenny Metaverse) DAO is a community dedicated to curate a top-scale digital art collection, with full members governance from acquisition to selling. It is built on the Unicly platform for tokenizing and trading NFT collections.
    
    Jenny operates through small councils. The DAO's authorized institutions and power relations between them (=governance) are defined in its approved Constitution.

resources.name: Machi X DAO
resources.description: Machi X is a collective of artists and patrons, curating and collecting digital art.

resources.name: MoonDAO
resources.description: MoonDAO aims to decentralize access to outer-space exploration and research. Governed by $MOONEY token holders, it plans to send one of its members on a spaceflight in 2022 using the proceeds of their lottery Tickets To Space NFT collection. By crowdfunding private space travelling, MoonDAO effectively facilitates a community of vested followers to the space ventures operating the flights.

resources.name: cadcad
resources.description: The cadcad DAO relates to a community curating the cadCAD Python package for complex system design, led by BlockScience. It currently registers1 voter and 1 transfer of funds.

resources.name: flamingo
resources.description: Flamingo is an investment DAO that supports, purchases, archives, collects, and possibly farms selected NFTs. It is controlled by its DAO within the boundaries of its Delaware LLC registration.

resources.name: MANTRA DAO
resources.description:
MantraDAO runs a lending-focused DeFi protocol to leverage the potential of multi-chain infrastructure & tools for chain-versatile assets and collateralled stablecoin to follow.
    At its current stage, the DAO is under the complete hold of its founder Council, with community Snapshot signalling. Its roadmap includes decentralizing governance.

resources.name: ShapeShift
resources.description: ShapeShitf is a crypto security hardware producer currently en-route becoming a DAO. Its Decentralized EXchange offers peer-to-peer swaps with increased user privacy.

resources.name: Hakt DAO
resources.description: Hakt DAO enhances safer De-Fi for all through security audit grants, bounty matching and stipends for whitehat hackers. It is funded through auctions of its own unique NFTs themed after major crypto hacking events.

resources.name: Rarible
resources.description: Rarbile is a platform for creators to mint, present and trade their NFT content. Its governance token is distributed as rewards for buying and selling on the platform.

resources.name: SOCEAN
resources.description: Socean is a non-custodial staking protocol which allows $SOL holders to participate in DeFi trading using its SOCN token they get upon staking, while still earning rewards on their staked $SOL. The protocol is to be upgraded and secured by its DAO, via token holders & team governance.

resources.name: StakeWise
resources.description: StakeWise runs Ethereum-only liquidity pools that initiate Ethereum 2.0 Proof-of-Stake validator nodes. Stakers are offered yields and opportunities to farm those yields accross DeFi.

resources.name: PartyDAO
resources.description: PartyDAO is a community hub for web3 product building. It is currently focused on PartyBid - a tool for permissionless collective purchase, fractionalization and co-ownership of NFTs, already integrated with major NFT marketplaces.

resources.name: Botto
resources.description: Botto is an AI-trained art generator. Every week, it creates 50 different AI-improved pieces to be voted on by Botto DAO members. One weekly piece is thus selected, minted and auctioned. Auction proceedings go to the Botto community.Botto's DAO community votes on its art via a combination of $BOTTO token and Voting Points that are allocated upon providing liquidity or staking BOTTO for the first time, and regenerate as long as one holds the native token.Protocol and ecosystem-related decisions are designated a different governance path. Protocol governance was initially put in the hands of the Botto artist (protocol, developers) for 6 months of a setup "grace period", to end on 07/04/2022.Meanwhile, off-chain channels for community governance have been deployed on Botto's (a) Discord threads "governance-discussion" and "forum-proposals", (b) governance Forum, and (c) Snapshot space.

resources.name: Alchemix
resources.description: Alchemix DAO controls the Alchemix protocol, a platform for permissionless creation of synthetic tokens that follow yield-bearing assets. The expected yield is counted as advance for the minted synths.

resources.name: Farmgod DAO
resources.description: Farmgod DAO is the issuer of NFT avatars and collectible components of its Deliland game set to utilize NFTs as DeFi assets. It is built on the Fantom blockchain and uses PaintSwap for NFTs minting, trading and farming.

resources.name: Cryptex
resources.description: Cryptex is a crypto token pegged to the total market cap of all crypto tokens and coins as sourced by its oracles. Its user-pooled collaterals farm yield while pegging. Currently in Beta.

resources.name: Unslashed
resources.description: Unslashed supplies insurance covers for typical crypto risks such as wallet exploits, exchange hacks, custody risks and more. It services protocols, DAOs and institutions.

resources.name: PegzDAO
resources.description: Pegz is a series of 100 unique NFT collectibles designed by artist Matt Furie. Every Peg character belongs to one of ten families, the rarest of which being the Pepers- based on Matt Furie's 2005 cartoon and by now seed-meme, Pepe the Frog. Pegz DAO aims to align holders, investors and supporters of this cultural ecosystem.In March 2022, Furie, PegzDAO and their related Chain Saw LLC were sued for $500,000 by a collector who bought the DAO owned "NFT FEELSGOODMAN Series 20, Card 50", that was featured as the DAO's unique offering. After the sale was completed, however, PegzDAO has freely released another 46 copies of the NFT to members and other addresses, which resulted with profits for the newly released and serious dilution for the collector. While the lawsuit claims the sellers have knowingly misled the buyer, on-record publications show that the information about other copies was made public, though not always fully stated, if at all. The legal case is underway at the time of writing.

resources.name: Silo
resources.description: Silo is a permissionless, non-custodial AMM protocol for lending and borrowing on users' liquidity pools.At the heart of the protocol stand its underlying assets' separate pools (Silos), isolated from each other so as to lend & borrow against specific pool-bridged assets rather than against pooled derivatives of pooled collaterals. This is meant to isolate the entire protocol from single-asset risks.Silo's idea was conceived during Sep. 2021, followed by a quick DAO deployed and Token auction. It is currently performing code audits for a coming Beta version, and further aiming to create its own future stablecoin.

resources.name: Conjure
resources.description: Conjure allows permissionless automatic creation of boundless synthetic assets, including, DeFi aggregators, legacy finance and real-world commodities indices.

resources.name: Lido
resources.description: Lido incentivizes staking of ETH for validation of Ethereum 2.0 beacon nodes, without locking the staked tokens while allowing them to farm yield. It runs an ecosystem grants program.

resources.name: Badger DAO
resources.description: Badger DAO BUIDLs to connect Bitcoin & DeFi, including a blockchain bridge and yield-earning liquidity pools wokring various DeFi protocols. On 2 Dec. 2021 it was hit with a major hack and is currently laboring to recover, eleavate security and reactivate.

resources.name: Uniswap
resources.description: Uniswap is a Decentralized EXchange that generates automatic markets of liquidity asset pairs. It allows for flash transactions and liquidity allocation by specific price margins.
